{"ts":"2026-07-15T06:22:25.256Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"append","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/body","value":"Why this exists: PR#565 (pm-cpja) shipped scanHistoryAuthorAttribution scanning ALL history with no window (src/sdk/author-attribution.ts). The 162 flagged events predate author discipline and can NEVER be repaired: history streams are append-only immutable proof, so rewriting authors is forbidden by design. Without a legacy/actionable split the warning is permanent noise that violates the every-warning-maps-to-an-actionable-owner invariant. Precedents: pm-2ler (dangling_dependency_references active-only gating with legacy informational count) and pm-e9zh (missing_close_reason legacy set, never hand-backfill). Remediation for NEW events is prevention only: PM_AUTHOR, global --author, or config author_default."},{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-15T06:22:25.256Z"}],"before_hash":"81742f6148125d581e656245e958fde6a508720c3eee695cb09fd938a5001f6d","after_hash":"ca96c4597b02069023df34886408d221533986806bb3a2af5f3b0bcd2d0ef9ba"}
